                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="arnhem_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a town in the Netherlands, on the River Rhine. A famous <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-second-world-war" title="Second World War definition"><span class="ndv">Second World War</span></a> battle took place there in 1944, when Allied forces tried, and failed, to capture a bridge over the Rhine. Thousands of people were killed. The battle was the subject of the film <span class="ei">A Bridge Too Far</span>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
